# Curator-promoted session artifacts live here.
# This file exists so the directory is tracked in git even when empty.
#
# Promotion is curator-driven: when the operator judges a session in
# .claude/session-artifacts/<id>/ to be a high-quality reference for
# future sessions, copy the whole directory in here under a descriptive
# name, e.g.:
#
#   .claude/session-artifacts/exemplars/multi-agent-subagent-anchoring/
#   .claude/session-artifacts/exemplars/scope-map-replace-default/
#
# Two purposes:
# 1. Curated reference shelf — "what does a good session look like."
# 2. Drift baseline — diff a recent session against an exemplar to detect
#    workflow degradation.
#
# No automation. No promotion mechanism. Just `cp -r` when something is
# worth keeping as a reference.
